version_description: This is is in the Key of F# without a capo
This is an Improvement based on Version 3, Updated Capo on 2nd and chords fixed.
Simple and complete capo version with easy chords in the right position.
A version found here, winged a bit to fit the original better, you'll notice the transition chords are very important.
I have performed this song quite a lot and tweaked it as i went along, and this version (to me) sounds the most like the original whilst at the same time still being easy to play.
Simpler Chords, Improved chord placement, Capo at 5 sounds better in a more casual environment and should be better for a wider range of voices to sing along to.
These are the chords that Alex Trimble plays in all acoustic performances of 'What You Know', specifically this one: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zsnUJBGxQAw.

song_name: A Broken Man And The Dawn

version_description: First version, includes all chords based on whole context and a strumming pattern which is acoustic-friendly.
